<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-1512] Incorporate GeoHash in contrib/spatial</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1512</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;Based on comments from Yonik and Ryan in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-773&quot; title=&quot;Incorporate Local Lucene/Solr&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-773&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;br/&gt;
GeoHash provides the ability to store latitude / longitude values in a single field consistent hash field.&lt;br/&gt;
Which elements the need to maintain 2 field caches for latitude / longitude fields, reducing the size of an index&lt;br/&gt;
and the amount of memory needed for a spatial search.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
